SIMPLE: placebo
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Placebo
<hw>Pla*ce"bo</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., I shall
please, fut. of <ets>placere</ets> to please.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(R. C. Ch.)</fld> <def>The first antiphon of the vespers for the
dead.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A prescription with no
pharmacological activity given to a patient to humor or satisfy the
desire for medical treatment.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>a dose of a compound having no
pharmacological activity given to a subject in a medical experiment as
part of a control experiment in a test of the effectiveness of another,
active pharmacological agent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To sing placebo</b></col>, <cd>to agree with one in his
opinion; to be complaisant to.</cd> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Placebo effect</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
